metadata.name: Hatchet: Uzumaki #22
metadata.description:
Hatchet: Uzumaki (æ¸¦å·») is the first piece in Hatchet; a generative art series that hatches an arrangement of segmented polygons generated via a Voronoi diagram. Uzumaki (Japanese for 'spiral') arranges it's polygons in a multi-armed spiral with varying arm lengths and twist intensities.

All pieces in Hatchet are composed to emulate the aesthetic of colored pencils on paper. Each piece is capable of exporting its hatch lines as a well-labeled SVG document. This will allow collectors interested in plotting to create physical renditions of their iteration.

The following key-press actions are supported on the token:
- 'r': Animate the erasure and re-drawing of the hatch lines.
- 's': Export the SVG document describing the arrangement of hatch lines.

metadata.name: Pearls #4
metadata.description:
Pearls is a generative minimal artwork made with 100% code in p5js.

This algorithm places perfectly round pearls into multiple stacked grids and connects them in a pleasing way. The small grids lead to interesting emerging patterns. Some see faces and fish, others see ancient hardware and elephants, and some just enjoy the minimal simplicity.

-- controls (in live view)
s: to save the current image
a: to play a small animation

-- some attributes
layout: 2x2 to 34x34
palette: genuary, monochrome red & purple, night
mode: ink, walk
bias: central, north, east, south, west
density: sparse, middle, dense
symmetry: none, vertical, horizontal, point
layer: 2 to 6

metadata.name: FORMAT #40
metadata.description:
A generative animated artwork by Unruly Unroll, 2022.  
Custom HTML, JavaScript and GLSL code.

This artwork is responsive and the canvas will adapt to the size and orientation of the browser window.

Interaction on desktop :
- Press the 'SPACE' key to pause/unpause the animation.
- Press the 'S' key to save the current frame to a PNG file.  
- Press the 'F' key or double-click to switch to full screen mode.  
- Press the 'ESC' key to exit full screen mode.  

Interaction on mobile :
- Tap the screen to pause/unpause the animation.
- Double-tap the screen to switch to full screen mode.  
- Tap the back button to exit full screen mode.

@UnrulyUnroll

metadata.name: Tendencies #34
metadata.description:
Tendencies is the first in a set of collections based on a month-long study of Edward Zajec, one of the early pioneers of generative art in the 1970s.

Zajec's generative work was motivated by redundancy in his paintings: "The monotony of the manual task and the limited number of variations which I was able to produce in a given time made me realize the inadequacy of traditional methods in dealing with our present reality." Tendencies was inspired by â€” and pays tribute to â€” one if Zajec's earliest forays into generative creation: a work titled RAM 10 V.15, which was written on an IBM 1620 and programmed in FORTRAN.

The title of the collection itself is a reference to the first exhibition of Zajec's RAM series, while the number of editions minted referencing the year Zajec put plotter to paper.

Made in p5js
Created December 2022
By @christine_hall

metadata.name: Backward Oscillations #4
metadata.description:
Laboratory of curious graphic studies.

Imagine an old file found near Weinar, containing the graphic research of a geometry enthusiast...

A geometric figure with each side composed of a certain number of points (between 10 and 100) undergoes a rotation.

A grain, or "granularity"  brings a pencil effect that gives the illusion of old archives rescued from a secret's Bauhaus laboratory. Old illustrations whose paper would have undergone the damage of time.

Features:
- Paper: yellowed, cracked and dry most of the time, but there were a few pages found with the marks of time bleached out.
- Basic shape type: Polygons, sometimes stars. 
- Symmetry: Perfectly symmetrical geometrical shapes, but not always!
- x' and y' : parameters for the deformation, based on the Lissajous equations. The value for x is very often 1, the other values are totally random between 1 and 10, but it seems that there are 30 too.
- Length Loop : Time to draw the shape, usually 800 frames but we have seen some at 400 frames and others at 1600. 
- Granularity: 100 levels of granularity.
- Sides or branches : Mostly between 3 and 5.
- Points per sides or branches : around 50 (Gaussian Standard Deviation : 15).

Controls:
[ENTER] to pause or restart playback.
[s] to download the image*.

*The maximum print size is limited by the resolution and power of your computer. See https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/how-to-print-generative-art to print at high resolutions.

Made with the javascript framework P5.js

JÃ©rÃ´me Mercier - @generativePunk - https://www.pizza-punk.com 
December, 2022

metadata.name: Flossom #93
metadata.description: This work is a research of flow fields, exploring generative art forms and colors. It uses various drawing methods, randomized color palettes, and layers of patterns to add multiple dimensions of variety to the work. Willing to create a visual blossom.
